# Camada Infrastructure

## Estrutura

```
src/infrastructure/
├── containers/
│   └── containers.py              # ApplicationContainer (DI)
├── entrypoint/http/
│   ├── routes/                    # APIRouter por domínio
│   └── middleware/                # Middlewares HTTP
└── persistence/
    └── repositories/              # Implementações MongoDB
```

## Container DI

```python
class RepositoryContainer(containers.DeclarativeContainer):
    mongodb_client = providers.Singleton(MongoDBClient, url=settings.MONGODB_URL)
    example_repository = providers.Singleton(
        MongoDBExampleRepository,
        db=mongodb_client.provided.db,
    )

class UseCaseContainer(containers.DeclarativeContainer):
    repository = providers.DependenciesContainer()
    create_example_use_case = providers.Singleton(
        CreateExampleUseCase,
        repository=repository.example_repository,
    )

class ApplicationContainer(containers.DeclarativeContainer):
    repository = providers.Container(RepositoryContainer)
    use_case = providers.Container(UseCaseContainer, repository=repository)

container = ApplicationContainer()
```

## Regras

- Infrastructure NUNCA contém regra de negócio.
- Infrastructure depende de Domain e Application — nunca o contrário.
- Mapear exceções de infra (pymongo, httpx) para `ApplicationException` aqui, nunca nos use cases.
- Cada router registrado no container antes de ser incluído no `app`.
